comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T09:40:10.713Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check: pm search --status all for @types/node 26.1.0/26.1.1, CodeQL 4.37.0, Dependabot #462/#465 found canonical historical unblocking lineage pm-2czc but no item for the current version refresh. This concrete batch links to that closed precedent and supersedes the two stale bot branches."
  "2026-07-10T09:58:01.513Z",codex-root,"Evidence: npm registry latest @types/node is 26.1.1 and lockfile integrity matches the registry. Official github/codeql-action v4.37.0 annotated tag peels to immutable commit 99df26d4f13ea111d4ec1a7dddef6063f76b97e9. Frozen install, TypeScript 6 typecheck, CI workflow contract suite, production audit, contract snapshot, ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static/docstring gate, token budget, docs/skills, secret scan, and 88-command package-first dogfood all pass. Full coverage: 270 files, 5,506 tests, statements 34380/34380, branches 24588/24588, functions 6882/6882, lines 33039/33039."
  "2026-07-10T10:07:14.948Z",codex-root,"Pre-push review correction: Greptile c3c227b6-2938-4f6a-b779-27fe90419cdc correctly identified that @types/node 26 would weaken the Node >=22.18.0 compile-time compatibility guard. Accepted: moved to current Node-22 patch 22.20.1 instead, retained engines.node, re-ran typecheck and workflow contracts, and removed the security tag so pm-changelog routes the maintenance entry accurately."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T09:58:02.248Z",codex-root,"GitHub consolidation: this batch supersedes stale Dependabot PR #462 (@types/node 26.1.0, while registry latest is 26.1.1) and behind-main PR #465 (CodeQL v4.37.0). Close both only after this combined current-version PR merges."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T09:58:02.982Z",codex-root,"Dependency-bot PRs can become obsolete between rebase and review. Re-read the live registry and upstream annotated tag, peel the tag to its commit, and validate the combined graph instead of merging individually green but stale branches."
